…which means that gold speculation or sudden influxes of gold into the economy can lead to currency crashes.
…since everything is about the relative price anyways.  The only difference is that under gold standard  gold miners control inflation…

Mentioning gold standard  you’ll notice a lot of libertarians like that idea  even though it’s been kind of horrible historically.
